@startuml C4_Pattern_ParallelTasks
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Parallel Execution (AND-Split/Join)

Boundary(workflow, "Workflow Execution") {
    Component(ynet_runner, "YNetRunner", "Orchestrator", "AND-split logic")
    Component(task_a, "Task A", "Branch 1", "Parallel execution")
    Component(task_b, "Task B", "Branch 2", "Parallel execution")
    Component(task_c, "Task C", "Branch 3", "Parallel execution")
    Component(and_split, "AND-Split", "Gateway", "Create branches")
    Component(and_join, "AND-Join", "Gateway", "Synchronize branches")
    Component(sync_point, "SynchronizationPoint", "Barrier", "Wait for all")
}

Boundary(execution, "Parallel Execution") {
    Component(vt_pool, "VirtualThreadPool", "Runtime", "×3 Virtual threads")
}

Boundary(persistence, "State") {
    Component(db, "Database", "Storage", "Branch states")
}

ynet_runner --> and_split: Triggers AND-split
and_split --> task_a: Creates branch A
and_split --> task_b: Creates branch B
and_split --> task_c: Creates branch C

task_a --> vt_pool: Executes on VT-A
task_b --> vt_pool: Executes on VT-B
task_c --> vt_pool: Executes on VT-C

vt_pool --> db: Saves state (A)
vt_pool --> db: Saves state (B)
vt_pool --> db: Saves state (C)

task_a --> sync_point: Completes
task_b --> sync_point: Completes
task_c --> sync_point: Completes

sync_point --> and_join: All ready
and_join --> ynet_runner: Continues

Note as N1
AND-Split: 1 → 3 tasks (parallel)
Execution: VirtualThreads (no blocking)
Synchronization: Barrier (wait all)
AND-Join: 3 → 1 task (merge)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
